

Recap:
  Postion, Parent inherit, Gradient

Topics:

  fonts, icons
    using different types of fonts, icons in webpage
  
  mesurements

    different mesurement units ( absolute & relative ) in css

    Absolute units: px - pixel, pt - point, pc - picas,
    1px = 1/96th of an inch

    1pt = point 1/72th of an inch

    1pc = picas 12 * 1pt or 1/6th of inch

    Relative Units: %, vh, vw, 
      1% -> 1 percent of the parent
      vw -> viewport width
        1vw -> 1 % viewport width
      vh -> viewport height
        1vh -> 1 % viewport height

      emphemeral units
      em, rem ---> root em
        1rem = fontsize of the root element ( Initial Containing Block )
        1em = fontsize of the parent element

  Overflow - hidden, scroll, auto, visible

    Handle over the overflowing contents

    visible ---> default value, does not modify the overflow and the overflow is visible 

    hidden ---> hides the overflowing content on both vertically and horizontally

    scroll ---> Gives scroll to see the overflowing by scrolling

    auto ---> Gives scroll only when there is overflow on particular axis


  display: none & visibility: hidden

    display: none   --------> removes the space as well the contents of the elements
                              i.e: remove the DOM element
    visibility: hidden  -------> Hides the contents of the element but the space of the element remains unoccupied  
